<refsect2 id="nautilus-burn-get-drive-monitor" role="function" condition="since:2.16">
<title>nautilus_burn_get_drive_monitor ()</title>
<indexterm zone="nautilus-burn-get-drive-monitor" role="2.16"><primary>nautilus_burn_get_drive_monitor</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="NautilusBurnDriveMonitor">NautilusBurnDriveMonitor</link>* nautilus_burn_get_drive_monitor
                                                        (void);</programlisting>
<para>
Get a reference to the drive monitor
</para>
<para>
Returns a pointer to the <link linkend="NautilusBurnDriveMonitor"><type>NautilusBurnDriveMonitor</type></link> singleton.
<link linkend="NautilusBurnDriveMonitor"><type>NautilusBurnDriveMonitor</type></link> is a singleton, this means it is guaranteed to
exist and be valid until <link linkend="nautilus-burn-shutdown"><function>nautilus_burn_shutdown()</function></link> is called. Consequently,
it doesn't need to be refcounted since nautilus-burn will hold a reference to
it until it is shut down.  It is created by <link linkend="nautilus-burn-init"><function>nautilus_burn_init()</function></link>.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> <link linkend="NautilusBurnDriveMonitor"><type>NautilusBurnDriveMonitor</type></link>

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist><para role="since">Since  2.16
</para></refsect2>
